<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2764</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Swiss Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sulzer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-30">November
                                    30, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of November 21, 1918, together with its enclosure,
                            regarding the wish of your Government to be appropriately represented at
                            the coming conferences, especially those dealing with topics in which
                            Switzerland has interests of a general or private character.</p>
                        <p>In reply, I beg to inform you that this Government has received with
                            sympathy the request of the Swiss Government and it is not in a position
                            to give a final reply until after arrival of the President in Paris.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>